Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.name: continuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.abstract: The marker that is used as a starting point for this metrics configuration list response. This value is present if it was sent in the request.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.name: isTruncated
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.abstract: Indicates whether the returned list of metrics configurations is complete. A value of true indicates that the list is not complete and the NextContinuationToken will be provided for a subsequent request.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.name: metricsConfigurationList
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.abstract: The list of metrics configurations for a bucket.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.name: nextContinuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketMetricsConfigurat.abstract: The marker used to continue a metrics configuration listing that has been truncated. Use the NextContinuationToken from a previously truncated list response to continue the listing. The continuation token is an opaque value that Amazon S3 understands.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.name: bucket
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.abstract: The name of the bucket containing the inventory configurations to retrieve.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.name: continuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.abstract: The marker used to continue an inventory configuration listing that has been truncated. Use the NextContinuationToken from a previously truncated list response to continue the listing. The continuation token is an opaque value that Amazon S3 understands.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.name: expectedBucketOwner
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.abstract: The account id of the expected bucket owner. If the bucket is owned by a different account, the request will fail with an HTTP 403 (Access Denied) error.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.name: continuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.abstract: If sent in the request, the marker that is used as a starting point for this inventory configuration list response.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.name: inventoryConfigurationList
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.abstract: The list of inventory configurations for a bucket.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.name: isTruncated
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.abstract: Tells whether the returned list of inventory configurations is complete. A value of true indicates that the list is not complete and the NextContinuationToken is provided for a subsequent request.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.name: nextContinuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketInventoryConfigur.abstract: The marker used to continue this inventory configuration listing. Use the NextContinuationToken from this response to continue the listing in a subsequent request. The continuation token is an opaque value that Amazon S3 understands.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.name: bucket
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.abstract: The name of the bucket from which analytics configurations are retrieved.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.name: continuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.abstract: The ContinuationToken that represents a placeholder from where this request should begin.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.name: expectedBucketOwner
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.abstract: The account id of the expected bucket owner. If the bucket is owned by a different account, the request will fail with an HTTP 403 (Access Denied) error.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.name: analyticsConfigurationList
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.abstract: The list of analytics configurations for a bucket.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.name: continuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.abstract: The marker that is used as a starting point for this analytics configuration list response. This value is present if it was sent in the request.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.name: isTruncated
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.abstract: Indicates whether the returned list of analytics configurations is complete. A value of true indicates that the list is not complete and the NextContinuationToken will be provided for a subsequent request.

Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.name: nextContinuationToken
Classes/AWSS3ListBucketAnalyticsConfigur.abstract: NextContinuationToken is sent when isTruncated is true, which indicates that there are more analytics configurations to list. The next request must include this NextContinuationToken. The token is obfuscated and is not a usable value.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html#/c.name: AND
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html#/c.abstract: This is used in a Lifecycle Rule Filter to apply a logical AND to two or more predicates. The Lifecycle Rule will apply to any object matching all of the predicates configured inside the And operator.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html#/c.name: prefix
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html#/c.abstract: Prefix identifying one or more objects to which the rule applies.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html#/c.name: tag
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html#/c.abstract: This tag must exist in the object’s tag set in order for the rule to apply.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleAndOperator.ht.name: prefix
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleAndOperator.ht.abstract: Prefix identifying one or more objects to which the rule applies.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleAndOperator.ht.name: tags
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleAndOperator.ht.abstract: All of these tags must exist in the object’s tag set in order for the rule to apply.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: abortIncompleteMultipartUpload
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: Specifies the days since the initiation of an incomplete multipart upload that Amazon S3 will wait before permanently removing all parts of the upload. For more information, see Aborting Incomplete Multipart Uploads Using a Bucket Lifecycle Policy in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: expiration
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: Specifies the expiration for the lifecycle of the object in the form of date, days and, whether the object has a delete marker.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: filter
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: The Filter is used to identify objects that a Lifecycle Rule applies to. A Filter must have exactly one of Prefix, Tag, or And specified.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: identifier
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: Unique identifier for the rule. The value cannot be longer than 255 characters.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: noncurrentVersionExpiration
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: Specifies when noncurrent object versions expire. Upon expiration, Amazon S3 permanently deletes the noncurrent object versions. You set this lifecycle configuration action on a bucket that has versioning enabled (or suspended) to request that Amazon S3 delete noncurrent object versions at a specific period in the object’s lifetime.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: noncurrentVersionTransitions
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: Specifies the transition rule for the lifecycle rule that describes when noncurrent objects transition to a specific storage class. If your bucket is versioning-enabled (or versioning is suspended), you can set this action to request that Amazon S3 transition noncurrent object versions to a specific storage class at a set period in the object’s lifetime.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: prefix
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: Prefix identifying one or more objects to which the rule applies. This is No longer used; use Filter instead.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: status
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: If ‘Enabled’, the rule is currently being applied. If ‘Disabled’, the rule is not currently being applied.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.name: transitions
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html#/c:objc(.abstract: Specifies when an Amazon S3 object transitions to a specified storage class.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html#/c.name: date
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html#/c.abstract: Indicates at what date the object is to be moved or deleted. Should be in GMT ISO 8601 Format.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html#/c.name: days
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html#/c.abstract: Indicates the lifetime, in days, of the objects that are subject to the rule. The value must be a non-zero positive integer.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html#/c.name: expiredObjectDeleteMarker
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html#/c.abstract: Indicates whether Amazon S3 will remove a delete marker with no noncurrent versions. If set to true, the delete marker will be expired; if set to false the policy takes no action. This cannot be specified with Days or Date in a Lifecycle Expiration Policy.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleConfiguration.html.name: rules
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies lifecycle configuration rules for an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.name: events
Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.abstract: The Amazon S3 bucket event for which to invoke the AWS Lambda function. For more information, see Supported Event Types in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.name: filter
Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.abstract: Specifies object key name filtering rules. For information about key name filtering, see Configuring Event Notifications in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.name: identifier
Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.abstract: An optional unique identifier for configurations in a notification configuration. If you don’t provide one, Amazon S3 will assign an ID.

Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.name: lambdaFunctionArn
Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the AWS Lambda function that Amazon S3 invokes when the specified event type occurs.

Classes/AWSS3JSONOutput.html#/c:objc(cs).name: recordDelimiter
Classes/AWSS3JSONOutput.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: The value used to separate individual records in the output. If no value is specified, Amazon S3 uses a newline character (‘\n’).

Classes/AWSS3JSONInput.html#/c:objc(cs)A.name: types
Classes/AWSS3JSONInput.html#/c:objc(cs)A.abstract: The type of JSON. Valid values: Document, Lines.

Classes/AWSS3InventorySchedule.html#/c:o.name: frequency
Classes/AWSS3InventorySchedule.html#/c:o.abstract: Specifies how frequently inventory results are produced.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.name: accountId
Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.abstract:
The account ID that owns the destination S3 bucket. If no account ID is provided, the owner is not validated before exporting data.

Although this value is optional, we strongly recommend that you set it to help prevent problems if the destination bucket ownership changes.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.name: bucket
Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the bucket where inventory results will be published.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.name: encryption
Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.abstract: Contains the type of server-side encryption used to encrypt the inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.name: format
Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.abstract: Specifies the output format of the inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.name: prefix
Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.abstract: The prefix that is prepended to all inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryFilter.html#/c:obj.name: prefix
Classes/AWSS3InventoryFilter.html#/c:obj.abstract: The prefix that an object must have to be included in the inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryEncryption.html#/c.name: SSEKMS
Classes/AWSS3InventoryEncryption.html#/c.abstract: Specifies the use of SSE-KMS to encrypt delivered inventory reports.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryEncryption.html#/c.name: SSES3
Classes/AWSS3InventoryEncryption.html#/c.abstract: Specifies the use of SSE-S3 to encrypt delivered inventory reports.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryDestination.html#/.name: s3BucketDestination
Classes/AWSS3InventoryDestination.html#/.abstract: Contains the bucket name, file format, bucket owner (optional), and prefix (optional) where inventory results are published.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: destination
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: Contains information about where to publish the inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: filter
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies an inventory filter. The inventory only includes objects that meet the filter’s criteria.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: identifier
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: The ID used to identify the inventory configuration.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: includedObjectVersions
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: Object versions to include in the inventory list. If set to All, the list includes all the object versions, which adds the version-related fields VersionId, IsLatest, and DeleteMarker to the list. If set to Current, the list does not contain these version-related fields.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: isEnabled
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies whether the inventory is enabled or disabled. If set to True, an inventory list is generated. If set to False, no inventory list is generated.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: optionalFields
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: Contains the optional fields that are included in the inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: schedule
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies the schedule for generating inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.name: CSV
Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.abstract: Describes the serialization of a CSV-encoded object.

Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.name: compressionType
Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.abstract: Specifies object’s compression format. Valid values: NONE, GZIP, BZIP2. Default Value: NONE.

Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.name: JSON
Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.abstract: Specifies JSON as object’s input serialization format.

Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.name: parquet
Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html#/c:.abstract: Specifies Parquet as object’s input serialization format.

Classes/AWSS3Initiator.html#/c:objc(cs)A.name: identifier
Classes/AWSS3Initiator.html#/c:objc(cs)A.abstract: If the principal is an AWS account, it provides the Canonical User ID. If the principal is an IAM User, it provides a user ARN value.

Classes/AWSS3IndexDocument.html#/c:objc(.name: suffix
Classes/AWSS3IndexDocument.html#/c:objc(.abstract: A suffix that is appended to a request that is for a directory on the website endpoint (for example,if the suffix is index.html and you make a request to samplebucket/images/ the data that is returned will be for the object with the key name images/index.html) The suffix must not be empty and must not include a slash character.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: bucket
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract:
The name of the bucket containing the object.

When using this API with an access point, you must direct requests to the access point hostname. The access point hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.s3-accesspoint.Region.amazonaws.com. When using this operation with an access point through the AWS SDKs, you provide the access point ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about access point ARNs, see Using Access Points in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

When using this API with Amazon S3 on Outposts, you must direct requests to the S3 on Outposts hostname. The S3 on Outposts hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.outpostID.s3-outposts.Region.amazonaws.com. When using this operation using S3 on Outposts through the AWS SDKs, you provide the Outposts bucket ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about S3 on Outposts ARNs, see Using S3 on Outposts in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: expectedBucketOwner
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: The account id of the expected bucket owner. If the bucket is owned by a different account, the request will fail with an HTTP 403 (Access Denied) error.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: ifMatch
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Return the object only if its entity tag (ETag) is the same as the one specified, otherwise return a 412 (precondition failed).

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: ifModifiedSince
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Return the object only if it has been modified since the specified time, otherwise return a 304 (not modified).

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: ifNoneMatch
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Return the object only if its entity tag (ETag) is different from the one specified, otherwise return a 304 (not modified).

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: ifUnmodifiedSince
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Return the object only if it has not been modified since the specified time, otherwise return a 412 (precondition failed).

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: partNumber
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Part number of the object being read. This is a positive integer between 1 and 10,000. Effectively performs a ‘ranged’ HEAD request for the part specified. Useful querying about the size of the part and the number of parts in this object.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: range
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract:
Downloads the specified range bytes of an object. For more information about the HTTP Range header, see http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec14.html#sec14.35.

Amazon S3 doesn’t support retrieving multiple ranges of data per GET request.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: requestPayer
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Confirms that the requester knows that they will be charged for the request. Bucket owners need not specify this parameter in their requests. For information about downloading objects from requester pays buckets, see Downloading Objects in Requestor Pays Buckets in the Amazon S3 Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: SSECustomerAlgorithm
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Specifies the algorithm to use to when encrypting the object (for example, AES256).

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: SSECustomerKey
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Specifies the customer-provided encryption key for Amazon S3 to use in encrypting data. This value is used to store the object and then it is discarded; Amazon S3 does not store the encryption key. The key must be appropriate for use with the algorithm specified in the x-amz-server-side-encryption-customer-algorithm header.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: SSECustomerKeyMD5
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: Specifies the 128-bit MD5 digest of the encryption key according to RFC 1321. Amazon S3 uses this header for a message integrity check to ensure that the encryption key was transmitted without error.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.name: versionId
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectRequest.html#/c:o.abstract: VersionId used to reference a specific version of the object.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: acceptRanges
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Indicates that a range of bytes was specified.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: cacheControl
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Specifies caching behavior along the request/reply chain.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: contentDisposition
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Specifies presentational information for the object.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: contentEncoding
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Specifies what content encodings have been applied to the object and thus what decoding mechanisms must be applied to obtain the media-type referenced by the Content-Type header field.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: contentLanguage
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: The language the content is in.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: contentLength
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Size of the body in bytes.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: contentType
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: A standard MIME type describing the format of the object data.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: deleteMarker
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Specifies whether the object retrieved was (true) or was not (false) a Delete Marker. If false, this response header does not appear in the response.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: ETag
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: An ETag is an opaque identifier assigned by a web server to a specific version of a resource found at a URL.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: expiration
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: If the object expiration is configured (see PUT Bucket lifecycle), the response includes this header. It includes the expiry-date and rule-id key-value pairs providing object expiration information. The value of the rule-id is URL encoded.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: expires
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: The date and time at which the object is no longer cacheable.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: lastModified
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Last modified date of the object

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: metadata
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: A map of metadata to store with the object in S3.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: missingMeta
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: This is set to the number of metadata entries not returned in x-amz-meta headers. This can happen if you create metadata using an API like SOAP that supports more flexible metadata than the REST API. For example, using SOAP, you can create metadata whose values are not legal HTTP headers.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: objectLockLegalHoldStatus
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Specifies whether a legal hold is in effect for this object. This header is only returned if the requester has the s3:GetObjectLegalHold permission. This header is not returned if the specified version of this object has never had a legal hold applied. For more information about S3 Object Lock, see Object Lock.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: objectLockMode
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: The Object Lock mode, if any, that’s in effect for this object. This header is only returned if the requester has the s3:GetObjectRetention permission. For more information about S3 Object Lock, see Object Lock.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: objectLockRetainUntilDate
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: The date and time when the Object Lock retention period expires. This header is only returned if the requester has the s3:GetObjectRetention permission.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: partsCount
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: The count of parts this object has.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: replicationStatus
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract:
Amazon S3 can return this header if your request involves a bucket that is either a source or destination in a replication rule.

In replication, you have a source bucket on which you configure replication and destination bucket where Amazon S3 stores object replicas. When you request an object (GetObject) or object metadata (HeadObject) from these buckets, Amazon S3 will return the x-amz-replication-status header in the response as follows:

  • If requesting an object from the source bucket Amazon S3 will return the x-amz-replication-status header if the object in your request is eligible for replication.

    For example, suppose that in your replication configuration, you specify object prefix TaxDocs requesting Amazon S3 to replicate objects with key prefix TaxDocs. Any objects you upload with this key name prefix, for example TaxDocs/document1.pdf, are eligible for replication. For any object request with this key name prefix, Amazon S3 will return the x-amz-replication-status header with value PENDING, COMPLETED or FAILED indicating object replication status.

  • If requesting an object from the destination bucket Amazon S3 will return the x-amz-replication-status header with value REPLICA if the object in your request is a replica that Amazon S3 created.

For more information, see Replication.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: requestCharged
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: If present, indicates that the requester was successfully charged for the request.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: restore
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract:
If the object is an archived object (an object whose storage class is GLACIER), the response includes this header if either the archive restoration is in progress (see RestoreObject or an archive copy is already restored.

If an archive copy is already restored, the header value indicates when Amazon S3 is scheduled to delete the object copy. For example:

x-amz-restore: ongoing-request="false", expiry-date="Fri, 23 Dec 2012 00:00:00 GMT"

If the object restoration is in progress, the header returns the value ongoing-request="true".

For more information about archiving objects, see Transitioning Objects: General Considerations.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: SSECustomerAlgorithm
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: If server-side encryption with a customer-provided encryption key was requested, the response will include this header confirming the encryption algorithm used.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: SSECustomerKeyMD5
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: If server-side encryption with a customer-provided encryption key was requested, the response will include this header to provide round-trip message integrity verification of the customer-provided encryption key.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: SSEKMSKeyId
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: If present, specifies the ID of the AWS Key Management Service (AWS KMS) symmetric customer managed customer master key (CMK) that was used for the object.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: serverSideEncryption
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: If the object is stored using server-side encryption either with an AWS KMS customer master key (CMK) or an Amazon S3-managed encryption key, the response includes this header with the value of the server-side encryption algorithm used when storing this object in Amazon S3 (for example, AES256, aws:kms).

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: storageClass
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract:
Provides storage class information of the object. Amazon S3 returns this header for all objects except for S3 Standard storage class objects.

For more information, see Storage Classes.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: versionId
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: Version of the object.

Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.name: websiteRedirectLocation
Classes/AWSS3HeadObjectOutput.html#/c:ob.abstract: If the bucket is configured as a website, redirects requests for this object to another object in the same bucket or to an external URL. Amazon S3 stores the value of this header in the object metadata.

Classes/AWSS3HeadBucketRequest.html#/c:o.name: bucket
Classes/AWSS3HeadBucketRequest.html#/c:o.abstract:
The bucket name.

When using this API with an access point, you must direct requests to the access point hostname. The access point hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.s3-accesspoint.Region.amazonaws.com. When using this operation with an access point through the AWS SDKs, you provide the access point ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about access point ARNs, see Using Access Points in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

When using this API with Amazon S3 on Outposts, you must direct requests to the S3 on Outposts hostname. The S3 on Outposts hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.outpostID.s3-outposts.Region.amazonaws.com. Classes/AWSS3Error.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3.name: message
Classes/AWSS3Error.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3.abstract: The error message contains a generic description of the error condition in English. It is intended for a human audience. Simple programs display the message directly to the end user if they encounter an error condition they don’t know how or don’t care to handle. Sophisticated programs with more exhaustive error handling and proper internationalization are more likely to ignore the error message.

Classes/AWSS3EncryptionConfiguration.htm.name: replicaKmsKeyID
Classes/AWSS3EncryptionConfiguration.htm.abstract: Specifies the ID (Key ARN or Alias ARN) of the customer managed customer master key (CMK) stored in AWS Key Management Service (KMS) for the destination bucket. Amazon S3 uses this key to encrypt replica objects. Amazon S3 only supports symmetric customer managed CMKs. For more information, see Using Symmetric and Asymmetric Keys in the AWS Key Management Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html#/c:objc(cs).name: encryptionType
Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: The server-side encryption algorithm used when storing job results in Amazon S3 (for example, AES256, aws:kms).

Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html#/c:objc(cs).name: KMSContext
Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: If the encryption type is aws:kms, this optional value can be used to specify the encryption context for the restore results.

Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html#/c:objc(cs).name: KMSKeyId
Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: If the encryption type is aws:kms, this optional value specifies the ID of the symmetric customer managed AWS KMS CMK to use for encryption of job results. Amazon S3 only supports symmetric CMKs. For more information, see Using Symmetric and Asymmetric Keys in the AWS Key Management Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.name: accessControlTranslation
Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.abstract: Specify this only in a cross-account scenario (where source and destination bucket owners are not the same), and you want to change replica ownership to the AWS account that owns the destination bucket. If this is not specified in the replication configuration, the replicas are owned by same AWS account that owns the source object.

Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.name: account
Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.abstract: Destination bucket owner account ID. In a cross-account scenario, if you direct Amazon S3 to change replica ownership to the AWS account that owns the destination bucket by specifying the AccessControlTranslation property, this is the account ID of the destination bucket owner. For more information, see Replication Additional Configuration: Changing the Replica Owner in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.name: bucket
Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.abstract: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the bucket where you want Amazon S3 to store the results.

Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.name: encryptionConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.abstract: A container that provides information about encryption. If SourceSelectionCriteria is specified, you must specify this element.

Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.name: metrics
Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.abstract: A container specifying replication metrics-related settings enabling metrics and Amazon S3 events for S3 Replication Time Control (S3 RTC). Must be specified together with a ReplicationTime block.

Classes/AWSS3Destination.html#/c:objc(cs.name: replicationTime

The name of the destination bucket.

When using this API with an access point, you must direct requests to the access point hostname. The access point hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.s3-accesspoint.Region.amazonaws.com. When using this operation with an access point through the AWS SDKs, you provide the access point ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about access point ARNs, see Using Access Points in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

When using this API with Amazon S3 on Outposts, you must direct requests to the S3 on Outposts hostname. The S3 on Outposts hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.outpostID.s3-outposts.Region.amazonaws.com. When using this operation using S3 on Outposts through the AWS SDKs, you provide the Outposts bucket ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about S3 on Outposts ARNs, see Using S3 on Outposts in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3ReplicateObjectRequest.html.name: replicateSource
Classes/AWSS3ReplicateObjectRequest.html.abstract:
Specifies the source object for the copy operation. You specify the value in one of two formats, depending on whether you want to access the source object through an access point:

  • For objects not accessed through an access point, specify the name of the source bucket and the key of the source object, separated by a slash (/). For example, to copy the object reports/january.pdf from the bucket awsexamplebucket, use awsexamplebucket/reports/january.pdf. The value must be URL encoded.

  • For objects accessed through access points, specify the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the object as accessed through the access point, in the format arn:aws:s3:<Region>:<account-id>:accesspoint/<access-point-name>/object/<key>. For example, to copy the object reports/january.pdf through access point my-access-point owned by account 123456789012 in Region us-west-2, use the URL encoding of arn:aws:s3:us-west-2:123456789012:accesspoint/my-access-point/object/reports/january.pdf. The value must be URL encoded.

    Amazon S3 supports copy operations using access points only when the source and destination buckets are in the same AWS Region.

    Alternatively, for objects accessed through Amazon S3 on Outposts, specify the ARN of the object as accessed in the format arn:aws:s3-outposts:<Region>:<account-id>:outpost/<outpost-id>/object/<key>. For example, to copy the object reports/january.pdf through outpost my-outpost owned by account 123456789012 in Region us-west-2, use the URL encoding of arn:aws:s3-outposts:us-west-2:123456789012:outpost/my-outpost/object/reports/january.pdf. The value must be URL encoded.

To copy a specific version of an object, append ?versionId=<version-id> to the value (for example, awsexamplebucket/reports/january.pdf?versionId=QUpfdndhfd8438MNFDN93jdnJFkdmqnh893). If you don’t specify a version ID, Amazon S3 copies the latest version of the source object.

Classes/AWSS3ReplicateObjectRequest.html.name: storageClass

The entity tag is an opaque string. The entity tag may or may not be an MD5 digest of the object data. If the entity tag is not an MD5 digest of the object data, it will contain one or more nonhexadecimal characters and/or will consist of less than 32 or more than 32 hexadecimal digits.

Classes/AWSS3CSVInput.html#/c:objc(cs)AW.name: fileHeaderInfo
Classes/AWSS3CSVInput.html#/c:objc(cs)AW.abstract:
Describes the first line of input. Valid values are:

  • NONE: First line is not a header.

  • IGNORE: First line is a header, but you can’t use the header values to indicate the column in an expression. You can use column position (such as _1, _2, ) to indicate the column (SELECT s._1 FROM OBJECT s).

  • Use: First line is a header, and you can use the header value to identify a column in an expression (SELECT "name" FROM OBJECT).

Classes/AWSS3CSVInput.html#/c:objc(cs)AW.name: quoteCharacter

A single character used for escaping when the field delimiter is part of the value. For example, if the value is a, b, Amazon S3 wraps this field value in quotation marks, as follows: " a , b ".

Type: String

Default: "

Ancestors: CSV

The bucket name to which the upload was taking place.

When using this API with an access point, you must direct requests to the access point hostname. The access point hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.s3-accesspoint.Region.amazonaws.com. When using this operation with an access point through the AWS SDKs, you provide the access point ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about access point ARNs, see Using Access Points in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

When using this API with Amazon S3 on Outposts, you must direct requests to the S3 on Outposts hostname. The S3 on Outposts hostname takes the form AccessPointName-AccountId.outpostID.s3-outposts.Region.amazonaws.com. When using this operation using S3 on Outposts through the AWS SDKs, you provide the Outposts bucket ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about S3 on Outposts ARNs, see Using S3 on Outposts in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.name: expectedBucketOwner
Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.abstract: The account id of the expected bucket owner. If the bucket is owned by a different account, the request will fail with an HTTP 403 (Access Denied) error.

Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.name: key
Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.abstract: Key of the object for which the multipart upload was initiated.

Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.name: requestPayer
Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.abstract: Confirms that the requester knows that they will be charged for the request. Bucket owners need not specify this parameter in their requests. For information about downloading objects from requester pays buckets, see Downloading Objects in Requestor Pays Buckets in the Amazon S3 Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.name: uploadId
Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadRequest.abstract: Upload ID that identifies the multipart upload.

Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadOutput..name: requestCharged
Classes/AWSS3AbortMultipartUploadOutput..abstract: If present, indicates that the requester was successfully charged for the request.

Classes/AWSS3AbortIncompleteMultipartUpl.name: daysAfterInitiation
Classes/AWSS3AbortIncompleteMultipartUpl.abstract: Specifies the number of days after which Amazon S3 aborts an incomplete multipart upload.

Classes/AWSS3AbortIncompleteMultipartUpl.name: AWSS3AbortIncompleteMultipartUpload
Classes/AWSS3AbortIncompleteMultipartUpl.abstract: Specifies the days since the initiation of an incomplete multipart upload that Amazon S3 will wait before permanently removing all parts of the upload. For more information, see Aborting Incomplete Multipart Uploads Using a Bucket Lifecycle Policy in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3AccelerateConfiguration.htm.name: AWSS3AccelerateConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3AccelerateConfiguration.htm.abstract: Configures the transfer acceleration state for an Amazon S3 bucket. For more information, see Amazon S3 Transfer Acceleration in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3AccessControlPolicy.html.name: AWSS3AccessControlPolicy
Classes/AWSS3AccessControlPolicy.html.abstract: Contains the elements that set the ACL permissions for an object per grantee.

Classes/AWSS3AccessControlTranslation.ht.name: AWSS3AccessControlTranslation
Classes/AWSS3AccessControlTranslation.ht.abstract: A container for information about access control for replicas.

Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsAndOperator.html.name: AWSS3AnalyticsAndOperator
Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsAndOperator.html.abstract: A conjunction (logical AND) of predicates, which is used in evaluating a metrics filter. The operator must have at least two predicates in any combination, and an object must match all of the predicates for the filter to apply.

Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3AnalyticsConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies the configuration and any analyses for the analytics filter of an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsFilter.html.name: AWSS3AnalyticsFilter
Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsFilter.html.abstract: The filter used to describe a set of objects for analyses. A filter must have exactly one prefix, one tag, or one conjunction (AnalyticsAndOperator). If no filter is provided, all objects will be considered in any analysis.

Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsS3BucketDestinatio.name: AWSS3AnalyticsS3BucketDestination
Classes/AWSS3AnalyticsS3BucketDestinatio.abstract: Contains information about where to publish the analytics results.

Classes/AWSS3Bucket.html.name: AWSS3Bucket
Classes/AWSS3Bucket.html.abstract: In terms of implementation, a Bucket is a resource. An Amazon S3 bucket name is globally unique, and the namespace is shared by all AWS accounts.

Classes/AWSS3BucketLifecycleConfiguratio.name: AWSS3BucketLifecycleConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3BucketLifecycleConfiguratio.abstract: Specifies the lifecycle configuration for objects in an Amazon S3 bucket. For more information, see Object Lifecycle Management in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3CORSConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3CORSConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3CORSConfiguration.html.abstract: Describes the cross-origin access configuration for objects in an Amazon S3 bucket. For more information, see Enabling Cross-Origin Resource Sharing in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3CORSRule.html.name: AWSS3CORSRule
Classes/AWSS3CORSRule.html.abstract: Specifies a cross-origin access rule for an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3CSVInput.html.name: AWSS3CSVInput
Classes/AWSS3CSVInput.html.abstract: Describes how an uncompressed comma-separated values (CSV)-formatted input object is formatted.

Classes/AWSS3CSVOutput.html.name: AWSS3CSVOutput
Classes/AWSS3CSVOutput.html.abstract: Describes how uncompressed comma-separated values (CSV)-formatted results are formatted.

Classes/AWSS3CloudFunctionConfiguration..name: AWSS3CloudFunctionConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3CloudFunctionConfiguration..abstract: Container for specifying the AWS Lambda notification configuration.

Classes/AWSS3CommonPrefix.html.name: AWSS3CommonPrefix
Classes/AWSS3CommonPrefix.html.abstract: Container for all (if there are any) keys between Prefix and the next occurrence of the string specified by a delimiter. CommonPrefixes lists keys that act like subdirectories in the directory specified by Prefix. For example, if the prefix is notes/ and the delimiter is a slash (/) as in notes/summer/july, the common prefix is notes/summer/.

Classes/AWSS3CompletedMultipartUpload.ht.name: AWSS3CompletedMultipartUpload
Classes/AWSS3CompletedMultipartUpload.ht.abstract: The container for the completed multipart upload details.

Classes/AWSS3CompletedPart.html.name: AWSS3CompletedPart
Classes/AWSS3CompletedPart.html.abstract: Details of the parts that were uploaded.

Classes/AWSS3Condition.html.name: AWSS3Condition
Classes/AWSS3Condition.html.abstract: A container for describing a condition that must be met for the specified redirect to apply. For example, 1. If request is for pages in the /docs folder, redirect to the /documents folder. 2. If request results in HTTP error 4xx, redirect request to another host where you might process the error.

Classes/AWSS3DefaultRetention.html.name: AWSS3DefaultRetention
Classes/AWSS3DefaultRetention.html.abstract: The container element for specifying the default Object Lock retention settings for new objects placed in the specified bucket.

Classes/AWSS3DeleteMarkerReplication.htm.name: AWSS3DeleteMarkerReplication
Classes/AWSS3DeleteMarkerReplication.htm.abstract:
Specifies whether Amazon S3 replicates the delete markers. If you specify a Filter, you must specify this element. However, in the latest version of replication configuration (when Filter is specified), Amazon S3 doesn’t replicate delete markers. Therefore, the DeleteMarkerReplication element can contain only <Status>Disabled</Status>. For an example configuration, see Basic Rule Configuration.

If you don’t specify the Filter element, Amazon S3 assumes that the replication configuration is the earlier version, V1. In the earlier version, Amazon S3 handled replication of delete markers differently. For more information, see Backward Compatibility.

Classes/AWSS3Destination.html.name: AWSS3Destination
Classes/AWSS3Destination.html.abstract: Specifies information about where to publish analysis or configuration results for an Amazon S3 bucket and S3 Replication Time Control (S3 RTC).

Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html.name: AWSS3Encryption
Classes/AWSS3Encryption.html.abstract: Contains the type of server-side encryption used.

Classes/AWSS3EncryptionConfiguration.htm.name: AWSS3EncryptionConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3EncryptionConfiguration.htm.abstract: Specifies encryption-related information for an Amazon S3 bucket that is a destination for replicated objects.

Classes.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3EndEvent.name: AWSS3EndEvent
Classes.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3EndEvent.abstract: A message that indicates the request is complete and no more messages will be sent. You should not assume that the request is complete until the client receives an EndEvent.

Classes/AWSS3ExistingObjectReplication.h.name: AWSS3ExistingObjectReplication
Classes/AWSS3ExistingObjectReplication.h.abstract: Optional configuration to replicate existing source bucket objects. For more information, see Replicating Existing Objects in the Amazon S3 Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3FilterRule.html.name: AWSS3FilterRule
Classes/AWSS3FilterRule.html.abstract: Specifies the Amazon S3 object key name to filter on and whether to filter on the suffix or prefix of the key name.

Classes/AWSS3Grantee.html.name: AWSS3Grantee
Classes/AWSS3Grantee.html.abstract: Container for the person being granted permissions.

Classes/AWSS3Initiator.html.name: AWSS3Initiator
Classes/AWSS3Initiator.html.abstract: Container element that identifies who initiated the multipart upload.

Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html.name: AWSS3InputSerialization
Classes/AWSS3InputSerialization.html.abstract: Describes the serialization format of the object.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3InventoryConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3InventoryConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies the inventory configuration for an Amazon S3 bucket. For more information, see GET Bucket inventory in the Amazon Simple Storage Service API Reference.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryDestination.html.name: AWSS3InventoryDestination
Classes/AWSS3InventoryDestination.html.abstract: Specifies the inventory configuration for an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryEncryption.html.name: AWSS3InventoryEncryption
Classes/AWSS3InventoryEncryption.html.abstract: Contains the type of server-side encryption used to encrypt the inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryFilter.html.name: AWSS3InventoryFilter
Classes/AWSS3InventoryFilter.html.abstract: Specifies an inventory filter. The inventory only includes objects that meet the filter’s criteria.

Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.name: AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestination
Classes/AWSS3InventoryS3BucketDestinatio.abstract: Contains the bucket name, file format, bucket owner (optional), and prefix (optional) where inventory results are published.

Classes/AWSS3InventorySchedule.html.name: AWSS3InventorySchedule
Classes/AWSS3InventorySchedule.html.abstract: Specifies the schedule for generating inventory results.

Classes/AWSS3JSONInput.html.name: AWSS3JSONInput
Classes/AWSS3JSONInput.html.abstract: Specifies JSON as object’s input serialization format.

Classes/AWSS3JSONOutput.html.name: AWSS3JSONOutput
Classes/AWSS3JSONOutput.html.abstract: Specifies JSON as request’s output serialization format.

Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.name: AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3LambdaFunctionConfiguration.abstract: A container for specifying the configuration for AWS Lambda notifications.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3LifecycleConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleConfiguration.html.abstract: Container for lifecycle rules. You can add as many as 1000 rules.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html.name: AWSS3LifecycleExpiration
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleExpiration.html.abstract: Container for the expiration for the lifecycle of the object.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html.name: AWSS3LifecycleRule
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRule.html.abstract: A lifecycle rule for individual objects in an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleAndOperator.ht.name: AWSS3LifecycleRuleAndOperator
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleAndOperator.ht.abstract: This is used in a Lifecycle Rule Filter to apply a logical AND to two or more predicates. The Lifecycle Rule will apply to any object matching all of the predicates configured inside the And operator.

Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html.name: AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter
Classes/AWSS3LifecycleRuleFilter.html.abstract: The Filter is used to identify objects that a Lifecycle Rule applies to. A Filter must have exactly one of Prefix, Tag, or And specified.

Classes/AWSS3LoggingEnabled.html.name: AWSS3LoggingEnabled
Classes/AWSS3LoggingEnabled.html.abstract: Describes where logs are stored and the prefix that Amazon S3 assigns to all log object keys for a bucket. For more information, see PUT Bucket logging in the Amazon Simple Storage Service API Reference.

Classes/AWSS3MetadataEntry.html.name: AWSS3MetadataEntry
Classes/AWSS3MetadataEntry.html.abstract: A metadata key-value pair to store with an object.

Classes/AWSS3Metrics.html.name: AWSS3Metrics
Classes/AWSS3Metrics.html.abstract: A container specifying replication metrics-related settings enabling metrics and Amazon S3 events for S3 Replication Time Control (S3 RTC). Must be specified together with a ReplicationTime block.

Classes/AWSS3MetricsAndOperator.html.name: AWSS3MetricsAndOperator
Classes/AWSS3MetricsAndOperator.html.abstract: A conjunction (logical AND) of predicates, which is used in evaluating a metrics filter. The operator must have at least two predicates, and an object must match all of the predicates in order for the filter to apply.

Classes/AWSS3MetricsConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3MetricsConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3MetricsConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies a metrics configuration for the CloudWatch request metrics (specified by the metrics configuration ID) from an Amazon S3 bucket. If you’re updating an existing metrics configuration, note that this is a full replacement of the existing metrics configuration. If you don’t include the elements you want to keep, they are erased. For more information, see PUT Bucket metrics in the Amazon Simple Storage Service API Reference.

Classes/AWSS3MetricsFilter.html.name: AWSS3MetricsFilter
Classes/AWSS3MetricsFilter.html.abstract: Specifies a metrics configuration filter. The metrics configuration only includes objects that meet the filter’s criteria. A filter must be a prefix, a tag, or a conjunction (MetricsAndOperator).

Classes/AWSS3MultipartUpload.html.name: AWSS3MultipartUpload
Classes/AWSS3MultipartUpload.html.abstract: Container for the MultipartUpload for the Amazon S3 object.

Classes/AWSS3NoncurrentVersionExpiration.name: AWSS3NoncurrentVersionExpiration
Classes/AWSS3NoncurrentVersionExpiration.abstract: Specifies when noncurrent object versions expire. Upon expiration, Amazon S3 permanently deletes the noncurrent object versions. You set this lifecycle configuration action on a bucket that has versioning enabled (or suspended) to request that Amazon S3 delete noncurrent object versions at a specific period in the object’s lifetime.

Classes/AWSS3NoncurrentVersionTransition.name: AWSS3NoncurrentVersionTransition
Classes/AWSS3NoncurrentVersionTransition.abstract: Container for the transition rule that describes when noncurrent objects transition to the STANDARD_IA, ONEZONE_IA, INTELLIGENT_TIERING, GLACIER, or DEEP_ARCHIVE storage class. If your bucket is versioning-enabled (or versioning is suspended), you can set this action to request that Amazon S3 transition noncurrent object versions to the STANDARD_IA, ONEZONE_IA, INTELLIGENT_TIERING, GLACIER, or DEEP_ARCHIVE storage class at a specific period in the object’s lifetime.

Classes/AWSS3NotificationConfiguration.h.name: AWSS3NotificationConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3NotificationConfiguration.h.abstract: A container for specifying the notification configuration of the bucket. If this element is empty, notifications are turned off for the bucket.

Classes/AWSS3NotificationConfigurationFi.name: AWSS3NotificationConfigurationFilter
Classes/AWSS3NotificationConfigurationFi.abstract: Specifies object key name filtering rules. For information about key name filtering, see Configuring Event Notifications in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3Object.html.name: AWSS3Object
Classes/AWSS3Object.html.abstract: An object consists of data and its descriptive metadata.

Classes/AWSS3ObjectIdentifier.html.name: AWSS3ObjectIdentifier
Classes/AWSS3ObjectIdentifier.html.abstract: Object Identifier is unique value to identify objects.

Classes/AWSS3ObjectLockConfiguration.htm.name: AWSS3ObjectLockConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3ObjectLockConfiguration.htm.abstract: The container element for Object Lock configuration parameters.

Classes/AWSS3ObjectLockLegalHold.html.name: AWSS3ObjectLockLegalHold
Classes/AWSS3ObjectLockLegalHold.html.abstract: A Legal Hold configuration for an object.

Classes/AWSS3ObjectLockRule.html.name: AWSS3ObjectLockRule
Classes/AWSS3ObjectLockRule.html.abstract: The container element for an Object Lock rule.

Classes/AWSS3OutputLocation.html.name: AWSS3OutputLocation
Classes/AWSS3OutputLocation.html.abstract: Describes the location where the restore job’s output is stored.

Classes/AWSS3OutputSerialization.html.name: AWSS3OutputSerialization
Classes/AWSS3OutputSerialization.html.abstract: Describes how results of the Select job are serialized.

Classes/AWSS3Owner.html.name: AWSS3Owner
Classes/AWSS3Owner.html.abstract: Container for the owner’s display name and ID.

Classes/AWSS3OwnershipControls.html.name: AWSS3OwnershipControls
Classes/AWSS3OwnershipControls.html.abstract: The container element for a bucket’s ownership controls.

Classes/AWSS3OwnershipControlsRule.html.name: AWSS3OwnershipControlsRule
Classes/AWSS3OwnershipControlsRule.html.abstract: The container element for an ownership control rule.

Classes/AWSS3Part.html.name: AWSS3Part
Classes/AWSS3Part.html.abstract: Container for elements related to a part.

Classes/AWSS3PolicyStatus.html.name: AWSS3PolicyStatus
Classes/AWSS3PolicyStatus.html.abstract: The container element for a bucket’s policy status.

Classes/AWSS3Progress.html.name: AWSS3Progress
Classes/AWSS3Progress.html.abstract: This data type contains information about progress of an operation.

Classes/AWSS3ProgressEvent.html.name: AWSS3ProgressEvent
Classes/AWSS3ProgressEvent.html.abstract: This data type contains information about the progress event of an operation.

Classes/AWSS3PublicAccessBlockConfigurat.name: AWSS3PublicAccessBlockConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3PublicAccessBlockConfigurat.abstract: The PublicAccessBlock configuration that you want to apply to this Amazon S3 bucket. You can enable the configuration options in any combination. For more information about when Amazon S3 considers a bucket or object public, see The Meaning of “Public” in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3QueueConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3QueueConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3QueueConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies the configuration for publishing messages to an Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) queue when Amazon S3 detects specified events.

Classes/AWSS3QueueConfigurationDeprecate.name: AWSS3QueueConfigurationDeprecated
Classes/AWSS3QueueConfigurationDeprecate.abstract: This data type is deprecated. Use QueueConfiguration for the same purposes. This data type specifies the configuration for publishing messages to an Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) queue when Amazon S3 detects specified events.

Classes/AWSS3Redirect.html.name: AWSS3Redirect
Classes/AWSS3Redirect.html.abstract: Specifies how requests are redirected. In the event of an error, you can specify a different error code to return.

Classes/AWSS3RedirectAllRequestsTo.html.name: AWSS3RedirectAllRequestsTo
Classes/AWSS3RedirectAllRequestsTo.html.abstract: Specifies the redirect behavior of all requests to a website endpoint of an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3ReplicationConfiguration.ht.name: AWSS3ReplicationConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3ReplicationConfiguration.ht.abstract: A container for replication rules. You can add up to 1,000 rules. The maximum size of a replication configuration is 2 MB.

Classes/AWSS3ReplicationRule.html.name: AWSS3ReplicationRule
Classes/AWSS3ReplicationRule.html.abstract: Specifies which Amazon S3 objects to replicate and where to store the replicas.

Classes/AWSS3ReplicationRuleAndOperator..name: AWSS3ReplicationRuleAndOperator
Classes/AWSS3ReplicationRuleAndOperator..abstract:
A container for specifying rule filters. The filters determine the subset of objects to which the rule applies. This element is required only if you specify more than one filter.

For example:

  • If you specify both a Prefix and a Tag filter, wrap these filters in an And tag.

  • If you specify a filter based on multiple tags, wrap the Tag elements in an And tag

Classes/AWSS3ReplicationRuleFilter.html.name: AWSS3ReplicationRuleFilter
Classes/AWSS3ReplicationRuleFilter.html.abstract: A filter that identifies the subset of objects to which the replication rule applies. A Filter must specify exactly one Prefix, Tag, or an And child element.

Classes/AWSS3ReplicationTime.html.name: AWSS3ReplicationTime
Classes/AWSS3ReplicationTime.html.abstract: A container specifying S3 Replication Time Control (S3 RTC) related information, including whether S3 RTC is enabled and the time when all objects and operations on objects must be replicated. Must be specified together with a Metrics block.

Classes/AWSS3ReplicationTimeValue.html.name: AWSS3ReplicationTimeValue
Classes/AWSS3ReplicationTimeValue.html.abstract: A container specifying the time value for S3 Replication Time Control (S3 RTC) and replication metrics EventThreshold.

Classes/AWSS3RequestProgress.html.name: AWSS3RequestProgress
Classes/AWSS3RequestProgress.html.abstract: Container for specifying if periodic QueryProgress messages should be sent.

Classes/AWSS3RoutingRule.html.name: AWSS3RoutingRule
Classes/AWSS3RoutingRule.html.abstract: Specifies the redirect behavior and when a redirect is applied. For more information about routing rules, see Configuring advanced conditional redirects in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3Rule.html.name: AWSS3Rule
Classes/AWSS3Rule.html.abstract: Specifies lifecycle rules for an Amazon S3 bucket. For more information, see Put Bucket Lifecycle Configuration in the Amazon Simple Storage Service API Reference. For examples, see Put Bucket Lifecycle Configuration Examples

Classes/AWSS3S3KeyFilter.html.name: AWSS3S3KeyFilter
Classes/AWSS3S3KeyFilter.html.abstract: A container for object key name prefix and suffix filtering rules.

Classes/AWSS3S3Location.html.name: AWSS3S3Location
Classes/AWSS3S3Location.html.abstract: Describes an Amazon S3 location that will receive the results of the restore request.

Classes/AWSS3SSEKMS.html.name: AWSS3SSEKMS
Classes/AWSS3SSEKMS.html.abstract: Specifies the use of SSE-KMS to encrypt delivered inventory reports.

Classes.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3SSES3.name: AWSS3SSES3
Classes.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3SSES3.abstract: Specifies the use of SSE-S3 to encrypt delivered inventory reports.

Classes/AWSS3ScanRange.html.name: AWSS3ScanRange
Classes/AWSS3ScanRange.html.abstract: Specifies the byte range of the object to get the records from. A record is processed when its first byte is contained by the range. This parameter is optional, but when specified, it must not be empty. See RFC 2616, Section 14.35.1 about how to specify the start and end of the range.

Classes/AWSS3SelectObjectContentEventStr.name: AWSS3SelectObjectContentEventStream
Classes/AWSS3SelectObjectContentEventStr.abstract: The container for selecting objects from a content event stream.

Classes/AWSS3SelectObjectContentRequest..name: AWSS3SelectObjectContentRequest
Classes/AWSS3SelectObjectContentRequest..abstract: Request to filter the contents of an Amazon S3 object based on a simple Structured Query Language (SQL) statement. In the request, along with the SQL expression, you must specify a data serialization format (JSON or CSV) of the object. Amazon S3 uses this to parse object data into records. It returns only records that match the specified SQL expression. You must also specify the data serialization format for the response. For more information, see S3Select API Documentation.

Classes/AWSS3SelectParameters.html.name: AWSS3SelectParameters
Classes/AWSS3SelectParameters.html.abstract: Describes the parameters for Select job types.

Classes/AWSS3ServerSideEncryptionByDefau.name: AWSS3ServerSideEncryptionByDefault
Classes/AWSS3ServerSideEncryptionByDefau.abstract: Describes the default server-side encryption to apply to new objects in the bucket. If a PUT Object request doesn’t specify any server-side encryption, this default encryption will be applied. For more information, see PUT Bucket encryption in the Amazon Simple Storage Service API Reference.

Classes/AWSS3SourceSelectionCriteria.htm.name: AWSS3SourceSelectionCriteria
Classes/AWSS3SourceSelectionCriteria.htm.abstract: A container that describes additional filters for identifying the source objects that you want to replicate. You can choose to enable or disable the replication of these objects. Currently, Amazon S3 supports only the filter that you can specify for objects created with server-side encryption using a customer master key (CMK) stored in AWS Key Management Service (SSE-KMS).

Classes/AWSS3SseKmsEncryptedObjects.html.name: AWSS3SseKmsEncryptedObjects
Classes/AWSS3SseKmsEncryptedObjects.html.abstract: A container for filter information for the selection of S3 objects encrypted with AWS KMS.

Classes/AWSS3StorageClassAnalysis.html.name: AWSS3StorageClassAnalysis
Classes/AWSS3StorageClassAnalysis.html.abstract: Specifies data related to access patterns to be collected and made available to analyze the tradeoffs between different storage classes for an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3StorageClassAnalysisDataExp.name: AWSS3StorageClassAnalysisDataExport
Classes/AWSS3StorageClassAnalysisDataExp.abstract: Container for data related to the storage class analysis for an Amazon S3 bucket for export.

Classes/AWSS3Tag.html.name: AWSS3Tag
Classes/AWSS3Tag.html.abstract: A container of a key value name pair.

Classes/AWSS3TopicConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3TopicConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3TopicConfiguration.html.abstract: A container for specifying the configuration for publication of messages to an Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) topic when Amazon S3 detects specified events.

Classes/AWSS3TopicConfigurationDeprecate.name: AWSS3TopicConfigurationDeprecated
Classes/AWSS3TopicConfigurationDeprecate.abstract: A container for specifying the configuration for publication of messages to an Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) topic when Amazon S3 detects specified events. This data type is deprecated. Use TopicConfiguration instead.

Classes/AWSS3Transition.html.name: AWSS3Transition
Classes/AWSS3Transition.html.abstract: Specifies when an object transitions to a specified storage class. For more information about Amazon S3 lifecycle configuration rules, see Transitioning Objects Using Amazon S3 Lifecycle in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.

Classes/AWSS3VersioningConfiguration.htm.name: AWSS3VersioningConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3VersioningConfiguration.htm.abstract: Describes the versioning state of an Amazon S3 bucket. For more information, see PUT Bucket versioning in the Amazon Simple Storage Service API Reference.

Classes/AWSS3WebsiteConfiguration.html.name: AWSS3WebsiteConfiguration
Classes/AWSS3WebsiteConfiguration.html.abstract: Specifies website configuration parameters for an Amazon S3 bucket.

Classes/AWSS3GetPreSignedURLRequest.html.name: AWSS3GetPreSignedURLRequest
Classes/AWSS3GetPreSignedURLRequest.html.abstract: The GetPreSignedURLRequest contains the parameters used to create

Classes/AWSS3TransferManager.html.name: AWSS3TransferManager
Classes/AWSS3TransferManager.html.abstract: High level utility for managing transfers to Amazon S3. S3TransferManager provides a simple API for uploading and downloading content to Amazon S3, and makes extensive use of Amazon S3 multipart uploads to achieve enhanced throughput, performance and reliability.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtility.html.name: AWSS3TransferUtility
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtility.html.abstract: A high-level utility for managing background uploads and downloads. The transfers continue even when the app is suspended. You must call + application:handleEventsForBackgroundURLSession:completionHandler: in the - application:handleEventsForBackgroundURLSession:completionHandler: application delegate in order for the background transfer callback to work.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityTask.html.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityTask
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityTask.html.abstract: The task object to represent a upload or download task.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityUploadTask.h.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityUploadTask
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityUploadTask.h.abstract: The task object to represent a upload task.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityMultiPartUpl.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityMultiPartUploadTask
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityMultiPartUpl.abstract: The task object to represent a multipart upload task.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityDownloadTask.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityDownloadTask
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityDownloadTask.abstract: The task object to represent a download task.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityExpression.h.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityExpression
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityExpression.h.abstract: The expression object for configuring a upload or download task.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityUploadExpres.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityUploadExpression
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityUploadExpres.abstract: The expression object for configuring a upload task.

Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityMultiPartUpl.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityMultiPartUploadExpression
Classes/AWSS3TransferUtilityMultiPartUpl.abstract: The expression object for configuring a Multipart upload task.

Classes.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3TransferUti.name: AWSS3TransferUtilityDownloadExpression
Classes.html#/c:objc(cs)AWSS3TransferUti.abstract: The expression object for configuring a download task.

Type%20Definitions.html.name: Type Definitions
Type%20Definitions.html.abstract: The following type definitions are available globally.
